content:
Install the CRM Analytics App Package to allow your mobile clients to easily connect to your org. This package contains the Connected App component that gives you control over who's logging in and how your mobile clients share images and links.

Available in Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience, with CRM Analytics available for an extra cost in Enterprise, Performance, and Unlimited Editions, as well as in Developer Edition.

To install, navigate to:
Production: https://login.salesforce.com/packaging/installPackage.apexp?p0=04tB0000000cHCH
Sandbox: https://test.salesforce.com/packaging/installPackage.apexp?p0=04tB0000000cHCH

Select Install for All Users. If you install the Connected App only for certain roles, then only those clients are subject to your policies.

All sharing options are enabled by default. To disable an option, add its attribute key and enter "false" for the attribute value. Supported attribute keys include:

* CACHE_QUERY_RESULTS: Store query cache results to disk
* OFFLINE_BETA: Store data for offline access
* SHARE_IMAGE_AIRDROP: Share images via AirDrop
* SHARE_LINK_NFC: Share links via Near Field Communication (NFC)
* SHARE_LINK_BLUETOOTH: Share links via Bluetooth

To view and control how mobile clients connect to your CRM Analytics-enabled org, from Setup, in the Quick Find box, enter Connected Apps, and then select Connect Apps OAuth Usage.

For extra security, use Mobile Device Management (MDM) with the option to show only authorized hosts. The "OnlyShowAuthorizedHosts" key allows you to hide the “Add New Account” plus sign in the mobile app.
title: Configure CRM Analytics on Mobile
